listBibl.bibl: Kolderup-Rosenvinge, Samling af gamle danske Love V 64-69

supportDesc.extent: 1 + 141 + 1 (the 141 folia are made up of 1–140 + 29bis). The following leaves are blank: fols 65r-68v, 86v-87v, 95v, 97, 113v and 121. 207 150 .

foliation.p: The manuscript is foliated in the top right-hand corners.

layout.p: Written in one column throughout with 21 to 33 lines per page. Running titles (until fol. 48v) and initials in red and green, rubrics (until fol. 53v) in red.

provenance.p:
A note in Árni Magnússon's hand has been pasted on the pastedown: Istud legisterium est elemosi
na Domini Birgeri Archiepiscopi
lundensis etc. pro usu sedis
Lundensis in Schania. ipso
die Nativitatis Joannis Ba
ptiste M. d. decimo quinto. Thus, according to this note, the Archbishop of Lund – Birger Gunnersen (c. 1440-1519) – owned the manuscript.

custEvent.p: The manuscript was lent to The Danish National Archives (Rigsarkivet), Copenhagen, for the use of Erik Kroman 15 May 1956 to 13 July 1962, 21 february 1963 to 10 November 1967 and 27 April to 17 July 1970.
The manuscript was lent to The Royal Library (Det Kongelige Bibliotek), Copenhagen, 13 November to 17 December 1967.
The manuscript was lent to The Danish National Archives (Rigsarkivet), Copenhagen, for the use of Sune Dalgård 22 November 1971 to 16 August 1983.

surrogates.p:
The manuscript was photographed in 1988 and The Arnamagnæan Collection keeps the following copies
microfilm (master), Neg. 768, from 1988.
Microfilm (archive), Pos. 703, from 1988.
Black and white prints, s.d.
